org.kite.annotations

Annotation Type Provided


  • @Target(value={METHOD,FIELD})
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Provided
    Marks that method or field of WiredService is available after connection to dependency injection.
    Note, that if you mark field with it - you have to worry about it's initialization, by the moment service is connected
    If you mark method with it - it has to be getter-like, with no parameters.

    Async:

    By setting async() type of exposing this method, you set the behaviour of calling interface, marked with this annotation. Examine AsyncType for better understanding. Default async value is AsyncType.NONE
    See Also:
    AsyncType, Wired, WiredService
